"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101180","Home Office","false","2014-10-30","<p>The data requested is not available. Information on prosecutions is held by the Crown Prosecution Service and is not relayed back to Action Fraud to correlate against reports.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-10-30T11:39:46.8404078Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101180/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101180/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101180/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-10-27","Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many successful prosecutions were made for cybercrimes reported to Action Fraud in each year since 2009.","false","Biography information for Julie Hilling","Bolton West","Julie Hilling","212020"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101181","Home Office","false","2014-10-30","<p>The National Fraud Intelligence Bureau had an establishment of 84 permanent members of staff in 2012-13, and the same number of permanent staff in 2013-14. <br><br>The National Fraud Intelligence Bureau is also complimented by officers and staff in other police forces and the National Crime Agency.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-10-30T11:40:39.7355898Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101181/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101181/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101181/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-10-27","National Fraud Intelligence Bureau","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many permanent members of staff were employed by the National Fraud Intelligence Bureau in (a) 2012-13 and (b) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Julie Hilling","Bolton West","Julie Hilling","212019"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101182","House of Commons Commission","false","2014-10-31","<p>The post of Serjeant at Arms was last advertised in 2012. The successful applicant was Lawrence Ward. Candidates applied in confidence: it is not the Commission's practice to disclose the names of the unsuccessful applicants as this would breach their expectation of confidentiality.</p>","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","John Thurso",,"2014-10-31T10:39:13.5266888Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101182/answer","Biography information for Viscount Thurso","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101182/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101182/answer",,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2014-10-27","Serjeant at Arms","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross representing the House of Commons Commission, who the candidates were for the post of Serjeant at Arms on the last occasion on which it was advertised.","false","Biography information for Michael Fabricant","Lichfield","Michael Fabricant","211941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101183","House of Commons Commission","false","2014-10-31","<p>The Commission acknowledges the challenges involved in changing the unique and complex system that serves over 2,200 screens across Parliament and 20 government departments, and commends the House Service for the smooth changeover. Engineering, project management, maintenance and commercial staff were involved, together with the suppliers and sub-contractors, and Parliament’s long-serving on-site Annunciator technicians. I have nothing to offer as reward beyond my heartfelt thanks.</p><p>The teams involved are delighted that this project has been singled out for acknowledgement by the hon. Member for Lichfield, and are grateful for his support in the early days of defining the system requirements, during his time on the Administration Committee.</p>","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","John Thurso",,"2014-10-31T11:00:33.4550206Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101183/answer","Biography information for Viscount Thurso","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101183/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101183/answer",,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2014-10-27","Television","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross representing the House of Commons Commission, if he will take steps to reward the teams who have installed and successfully delivered digital television feeds including BBC local news and European Parliament, Committee Room, Welsh Assembly, and Scottish Parliament proceedings to offices on the Estate.","false","Biography information for Michael Fabricant","Lichfield","Michael Fabricant","211942"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101184","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-30","<p>MoD personnel are performing an invaluable role in the UK response to the Ebola crisis, working alongside DFID and NGO staff. All deployments are consistent with the Oslo Guidelines which define how military assets can be used for humanitarian purposes.</p><p> </p><p>MoD and DFID have worked together in this way in Haiti, Chile and Indonesia, cyclones in Burma and the Philippines, flooding in Pakistan, the conflict in Iraq and the current Ebola outbreak in West Africa.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening","212058","2014-10-30T17:04:53.0514573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101184/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101184/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101184/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-10-27","Military Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the contribution by the Minister of State for the Armed Forces on 20 October 2014, Official Report, column 66, on troop deployment: West Africa, on how many previous occasions her Department has funded support from the armed forces for humanitarian efforts; and whether it is her policy that such support will continue to be so funded in future.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","212057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101185","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-30","<p>MoD personnel are performing an invaluable role in the UK response to the Ebola crisis, working alongside DFID and NGO staff. All deployments are consistent with the Oslo Guidelines which define how military assets can be used for humanitarian purposes.</p><p> </p><p>MoD and DFID have worked together in this way in Haiti, Chile and Indonesia, cyclones in Burma and the Philippines, flooding in Pakistan, the conflict in Iraq and the current Ebola outbreak in West Africa.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening","212057","2014-10-30T17:04:53.434856Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101185/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101185/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101185/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-10-27","Military Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the contribution by the Minister of State for the Armed Forces on 20 October 2014, Official Report, column 66, on troop deployment: West Africa, whether it is normal practice of her Department to provide funding for support from the armed forces for humanitarian relief.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","212058"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101186","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-30","<p>DFID is co-funding clinical trials to find a safe vaccine for Ebola as well as providing critical care on the ground. Britain is a world leader in medical research and mobilising our unique strengths to find a vaccine could be pivotal to containing Ebola and preventing future outbreaks.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening","212114 ; 212115","2014-10-30T17:05:44.8974534Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101186/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101186/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101186/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-10-27","Ebola","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much the Government is spending on accelerating the development of vaccines and medicines for Ebola.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","212144"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101187","Department for International Development","false","2014-11-03","<p>The UK is leading the international response to Ebola in Sierra Leone. This outbreak of Ebola is unprecedented in scale and highlights the vital importance of strong public healthcare systems. The UK is the biggest bilateral donor to Sierra Leone and commenced a major health systems programme in 2012.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-11-03T11:38:22.0078627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101187/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101187/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101187/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-10-27","Ebola","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps the Government is taking to encourage long-term measures to bring about systemic changes required to better cope with future Ebola outbreaks.","false","Biography information for Naomi Long","Belfast East","Naomi Long","212085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101188","Department for International Development","false","2014-11-03","<p>DFID has not entered into any Private Finance Initiative projects (PFIs) for the period 1997 to 2010.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-11-03T11:38:53.8759275Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101188/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101188/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101188/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-10-27","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many private finance initiative projects her Department contracted for in each year from 1997 to 2010.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","212100"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101189","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-30","<p>DFID is co-funding clinical trials to find a safe vaccine for Ebola as well as providing critical care on the ground. Britain is a world leader in medical research and mobilising our unique strengths to find a vaccine could be pivotal to containing Ebola and preventing future outbreaks.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening","212115 ; 212144","2014-10-30T17:05:44.5656103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101189/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101189/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101189/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-10-27","Ebola","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps the Government is taking to increase the production of promising Ebola drugs and vaccines and to negotiate the prices of those drugs and vaccines.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","212114"
