"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101221","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-11-03","<p /> <p>The “Men’s Sheds movement”, which began in Australia, aims to improve the health and wellbeing of men through providing inclusive environments where members can share tools, resources, skills and engage in personal and community projects. The Department has no plans to carry out any formal assessment of the effectiveness of the Men’s Sheds movement.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-11-03T16:48:48.6047972Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101221/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101221/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101221/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-27","Employment: Males","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 1 September 2014 to Question 206874, if his Department will make an assessment of the effectiveness of Men's Sheds movement on (a) increasing confidence and volunteering, (b) reducing isolation and mental ill health and (c) improving job readiness for the unemployed.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","212116"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101222","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-11-03","<p>People with Parkinson’s and other progressive conditions receive general financial provision towards costs, including heating, through Attendance Allowance, Disability Living Allowance (DLA) or Personal Independence Payment (PIP).</p><p> </p><p>Additional help is available to those entitled to income-related benefits - such as Employment and Support Allowance - through the support component and additional disability premiums.</p><p> </p><p>Help is also available through Cold Weather Payments, and this winter, over 2 million low income households will receive a bill rebate through the Warm Home Discount Scheme.</p><p> </p><p>Winter Fuel Payments also provide assurance to older people, who may suffer the worst impacts of a progressive condition, so that they can keep warm during the winter months.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-11-03T15:49:15.4971337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101222/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101222/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101222/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-27","Heating","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what support his Department makes available to ensure that people with (a) Parkinson's and (b) other progressive conditions are able to adequetely heat their home; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","212129"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101223","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-11-03","<p>I refer the hon. member to the Written Ministerial Statement made by my Rt. Hon. Friend, Iain Duncan Smith on of Monday 13th October 2014.</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/documents/commons-vote-office/2014-October/13th%20October/17.DWP-welfare-reform.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/documents/commons-vote-office/2014-October/13th%20October/17.DWP-welfare-reform.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>DWP are not setting targets for numbers in receipt of Universal Credit at various points in time. Final numbers will vary according to a number of factors such as the economic circumstances over time and behavioural change of claimants.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-11-03T17:54:37.1185644Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101223/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101223/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101223/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-27","Universal Credit: Barrow in Furness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in Barrow and Furness constituency he expects to have transferred to universal credit by 1 January 2015.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","212064"
