"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100743","Home Office","false","2014-10-29","<p>Home Office Ministers have received no representations relating to the police response to the demonstration in Parliament Square on 21 October.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-10-29T11:13:05.3271457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100743/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100743/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100743/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-10-23","Parliament Square: Demonstrations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what representations she has received on the police response to the demonstration in Parliament Square on 21 October 2014; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","211761"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100744","Home Office","false","2014-10-29","<p>The Home Office has not issued any guidance to the police. The City of London Police will second police officers to the Food Crime Unit as part of their role as the national lead for fraud. It is the responsibility of the College of Policing's national policing business areas to appoint, as appropriate a national business policing lead for this work and to secure the engagement of forces nationally with this initiative.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-10-29T11:12:41.7666431Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100744/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100744/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100744/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-10-23","Food: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what guidance her Department issues to the police on co-operation with the Food Standards Agency and the new Food Crime Unit; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Baroness McIntosh of Pickering","Thirsk and Malton","Miss Anne McIntosh","211751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100745","Home Office","false","2014-10-28","<p>We keep the family Immigration Rules under regular review in light of all feedback on their operation. However, we have no plans to lower the minimum income threshold required to bring family members to the UK under those rules. In its 11 July 2014 judgment in MM and Others the Court of Appeal upheld the lawfulness of the requirement and found that it strikes a fair balance between the interests of those affected and the community in general.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-10-28T14:18:27.0297433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100745/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100745/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100745/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-10-23","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent representations she has received on lowering the minimum income threshold limit required by those wishing to bring family members to the UK.","false","Biography information for Joan Walley","Stoke-on-Trent North","Joan Walley","211715"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100746","HM Treasury","false","2014-10-30","<p>The 4<sup>th</sup> EU Anti-Money Laundering Directive transposes the global standards on anti-money laundering and counter-terrorism finance set by the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) in 2012. These standards further embed the risk-based approach, which allow obliged entities, including companies, to adopt anti-money laundering checks which are best suited to the risk they face in their everyday business. This allows for more proportionate and balanced anti-money laundering regimes across the EU including in the UK.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Directive is currently in its last stage of negotiations. The UK government is committed to publishing an impact assessment and to consulting on the implementation of the Directive before transposing its new requirements into UK legislation, in line with better regulation principles. This timing is necessary to ensure that any Impact Assessment accurately reflects any changes to the draft legislation agreed in negotiations.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-10-30T16:46:41.4355653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100746/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100746/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100746/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-10-23","Money Laundering: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of the proposed revision of EU Anti-Money Laundering Directive on individuals and companies in the UK.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","211714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100747","Home Office","false","2014-10-29","<p>Fraud is a group of offences that consists of several different offence types. Fraud offences have always been recorded as notifiable offences. There has not been any recent major reclassification of these offences.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-10-29T13:30:29.8426881Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100747/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100747/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100747/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-10-23","Fraud","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, for what reason her Department has reclassified fraud as a notifiable recorded offence.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","211711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100748","Cabinet Office","false","2014-10-28","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2014-10-28T15:07:54.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100748/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100748/answer","PQ 211712 ONS 367.pdf","PQ 211712 ONS 367.pdf","ONS Letter to Member - Fraud Level","ONS Letter to Member - Fraud Level","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100748/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-10-23","Fraud","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the fraud level was in each of the last six years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","211712"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100749","Home Office","false","2014-10-30","<p>The National Crime Recording Standard (NCRS) governs the recording of Notifiable Offences by the Police. There have been no changes to NCRS since 2010.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-10-30T11:45:09.8433049Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100749/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100749/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100749/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-10-23","Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what changes have been made to the process of recording notifiable recorded crime categories since 2010.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","211713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100750","Home Office","false","2014-10-29","<p>The Childbase database ceased to be active in 2011 and is no longer live. All forces have access to the interim National Hash Set Database which will be replaced by the Child Abuse Image Database (CAID). The CAID is being developed to support analysis by police of devices seized during investigations; to support victim identification; and to provide hash set data to the internet industry, to allow them to remove these appalling images from their networks.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-10-29T13:36:08.7199845Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100750/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100750/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100750/answer","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100750/answer/previousversion/24622","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-10-23","Offences against Children: Databases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what her policy is on the future of the Childbase database of known online child abuse; how she envisages this database interacting with the Child Abuse Image Database; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","211722"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100751","Home Office","false","2014-10-29","<p>Departmental spend on commissioning the Child Abuse Image Database (CAID) for the first year is £1,473,179, which is being recharged to police forces. It is estimated that CAID will save the police £7.474 million by March 2017 by speeding up police processes.<br><br>The project has been developed using data from Interpol and, where appropriate, this information will be included in the initial database load for CAID.<br><br>The CAID system will be available to all police forces in the UK and National Crime Agency – Child Exploitation and Online Protection (NCA-CEOP) Command via the police secure network. All forces will be accredited to access this data supported by the Home Office project team and security advisers. The CAID system allows the use of forces’ existing image grading and hashing software. <br><br>Any additional software needed to access CAID and to upload new material from the forces/NCA-CEOP Command to the database is provided as part of the central project at no cost to the forces. <br><br>Each force is responsible for its own set-up costs to establish the connectivity of their force High Tech Crime Unit or Grading Unit in an <br>enhanced, secure way to the police secure network that already exists in their forces.<br><br>It is expected that the CAID will cost forces approximately £20,000 per year in service costs (which are used to maintain and improve the database). This cost has been agreed with the National Policing lead for Child Protection and Abuse Investigation.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-10-29T13:37:13.9100917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100751/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100751/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100751/answer","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100751/answer/previousversion/24642","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-10-23","Offences against Children: Databases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much her Department has spent on commissioning the Child Abuse Image Database; whether this database will include all image-data known to Interpol; what steps she has taken to ensure that police forces can access this database; what specialist software regional police forces will require to access this database; and what additional funds she is making available to cover the costs of such software.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","211721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100752","Home Office","false","2014-10-29","<p>A number of police forces are using predictive policing techniques, particularly to reduce crimes like burglary. The Home Office has undertaken no <br>formal assessment of these techniques, but the College of Policing has plans to release a technical assessment of different predictive crime mapping models and software. This will inform police forces’ decisions about appropriate analytical tools and techniques.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-10-29T11:13:29.5603244Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100752/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100752/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100752/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-10-23","Crime Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the effectiveness of the use of predictive analytics as a law enforcement tool.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","211675"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100753","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-28","<p>The UK is supporting the Social Mobilisation Action Consortium (SMAC) as part of its response to Ebola in Sierra Leone. This consortium focuses on achieving behaviour change to address a range of high risk practices to prevent and contain the spread of Ebola. Partners of the consortium, who include the Centre for Disease Control, provide technical advice on how to avoid infection. As well as avoiding contact with blood and bodily fluids of an infected person and ensuring safe funeral practices, this includes taking steps not to eat or handle bushmeat. We are also tracking knowledge of risk behaviours and transmission routes through a survey administered through the consortium in order to plan our behaviour change activities accordingly.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-10-28T16:23:14.0890018Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100753/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100753/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100753/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-10-23","Meat: Wildlife","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to raise awareness of the dangers of eating bushmeat in those countries where it is currently practised.","false","Biography information for Graham Stuart","Beverley and Holderness","Mr Graham Stuart","211777"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100754","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-10-30","<p>A response to the right hon. Member for Manchester, Gorton was sent on Tuesday 21 October 2014.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-10-30T15:59:22.1284742Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100754/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100754/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100754/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-10-23","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when he intends to reply to the letter to him dated 17 September 2014 from the right hon. Member for Manchester, Gorton with regard to Mrs M Lawson.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Kaufman","Manchester, Gorton","Sir Gerald Kaufman","211688"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100755","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-10-30","<p>HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service keeps the use of its estate under review in order to make the best use of its resources for users and taxpayers alike.</p><p> </p><p>The decision to close Rhyl County Court and move its work to Prestatyn Magistrates’ Court was announced by the Lord Chancellor in December 2010. The closure required enabling work at Prestatyn Magistrates' Court to accommodate the additional work, which has not yet been finalised. The court will not close until this work has been concluded. The effects on staff and levels of service were considered in response to the consultation and will form part of any closure implementation plan.</p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-10-30T16:17:33.406747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100755/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100755/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100755/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-10-23","Courts: Clwyd","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what progress has been made on the closure of courts in the Vale of Clwyd; and what assessment he has made of the effect of such closures on staff numbers and levels of service.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","211759"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100756","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-10-30","<p>I am in regular contact with the Irish Government and discuss a range of issues of economic and political importance, including legacy issues such as the Smithwick Tribunal.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-10-30T13:21:28.8956253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100756/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100756/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100756/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-10-23","Smithwick Tribunal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions she has had with the Irish government on the findings of the Smithwick Tribunal.","false","Biography information for Sir Jeffrey M. Donaldson","Lagan Valley","Mr Jeffrey M. Donaldson","211716"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100757","Department for Transport","false","2014-10-30","<p>In terms of future investment planning for the strategic road network, the Highways Agency is currently conducting its route strategy process to establish operational and investment priorities for all routes on the strategic road network. It is through this process that improvements to the A64 between York and Scarborough will be considered. The route strategy work is due for completion in March 2015 and will help inform the Department’s road investment strategy which we aim to complete before the end of this year.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2014-10-30T12:14:03.1434366Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100757/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100757/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100757/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-10-23","A64","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will provide funding for road improvements and a dual carriageway for the A64 between York and Scarborough; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Baroness McIntosh of Pickering","Thirsk and Malton","Miss Anne McIntosh","211749"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100758","Department for Transport","false","2014-10-30","<p>As the aviation regulator, the Civil Aviation Authority (CAA) has its own internal performance targets for processing licence applications.</p><p> </p><p>The CAA publishes its code of practice on its website. This sets out the standards and the levels of service which both the aviation industry and individuals may expect. Specifically – under Approval, certification and licensing service standards – the CAA say ‘Personnel Licences will be issued within ten working days’.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Transport does not provide any additional guidance on this issue.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-10-30T14:13:56.729599Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100758/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100758/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100758/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-10-23","Aviation: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what guidance his Department issues to the Civil Aviation Authority on the amount of time that body should take to process applications for licences.","false","Biography information for David Mowat","Warrington South","David Mowat","211695"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100759","Department for Transport","false","2014-10-30","<p>The Government has made no such assessment. Airports, and the airlines that use them, operate in a competitive environment and it is for them to take commercial decisions on the services that they offer. The Spanish partner, Ferrovial, already had an interest in these airports through its shareholding in Heathrow Airport Holdings Limited (formerly BAA).</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-10-30T16:01:03.511188Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100759/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100759/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100759/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-10-23","Aviation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the potential effects on (a) regional air routes to Northern Ireland and (b) other regional UK routes of the sale of Aberdeen, Glasgow and Southampton airports to a Spanish and Australian consortium.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","211666"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100760","Department for Transport","false","2014-10-30","<p>My Noble Friend Baroness Kramer, Minister for Local Transport has recently completed a review of the use of a derogation applied under EU Regulation 181/2011 (concerning bus and coach passenger rights) exempting bus and coach drivers from undertaking mandatory disability awareness training.</p><p> </p><p>To inform this review, she wrote to bus industry representatives, disability stakeholders and charities seeking their input, to determine whether drivers are receiving adequate disability awareness training under the current voluntary arrangement.</p><p> </p><p>Having received and considered many comprehensive responses, the findings have been shared with Ministerial colleagues who are discussing how best to proceed.</p><p> </p><p>While these discussions continue, officials will place a summary of all responses received in relation to the review on the Government’s website as a matter of priority.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2014-10-30T12:12:52.517515Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100760/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100760/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100760/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-10-23","Bus Services: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will review the decision to postpone the implementation of the driver training elements of EU regulation No. 181/2011 for up to four years.","false","Biography information for Joan Walley","Stoke-on-Trent North","Joan Walley","211763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100761","Women and Equalities","false","2014-10-28","<p>I receive regular representations on many issues including the role of women in public life.</p><p>We are removing barriers that prevent women from progressing in public life. For example, the Government has established the Centre for Public Appointments (CPA) in the Cabinet Office to ensure best practice is followed. As a result, the proportion of new female appointees to public boards has increased to 39%. We have also supported political parties to increase women’s representation thorough a combination of legislative and voluntary measures.</p><p> </p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson",,"2014-10-28T09:03:28.8801937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100761/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100761/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100761/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2014-10-23","Females: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Ministers for Women and Equalities, what recent representations she has received on the role of women in public life; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Baroness McIntosh of Pickering","Thirsk and Malton","Miss Anne McIntosh","211750"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100762","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-28","<p>Departmental statisticians are continuing to develop measures around clearance times and waiting times to ensure they provide a rounded and representative picture of personal independence payment performance, improvement activity and the claimants’ experience. These statistics will be published when they are ready, with the release pre-announced in line with United Kingdom Statistics Authority release protocols.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper","211677","2014-10-28T14:04:45.6034117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100762/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100762/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100762/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-23","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what average length of time his Department took to process a personal independence payment from (a) a motor neurone disease sufferer and (b) another disabled person since the introduction.","false","Biography information for Liz Kendall","Leicester West","Liz Kendall","211729"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100763","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-28","<p>Disability Living Allowance claimants who are asked to claim Personal Independence Payment will be assessed by an independent health professional. No assessments for Personal Independence Payment are currently carried out over the telephone.</p><p> </p><p>A health professional carrying out a review of paper-evidence may telephone the claimant to gather specific additional information to support their considerations.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-10-28T17:37:00.7362658Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100763/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100763/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100763/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-23","Disability Living Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of disability living allowance reassessments are conducted over the telephone.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","211706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100764","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-28","<p /> <p>The sourcing for suitable volunteer mentors is the responsibility of New Enterprise Allowance providers. Providers must ensure that mentors have the right skills and experience to provide business mentoring and support the participants into self-employment.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-10-28T15:51:02.1742325Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100764/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100764/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100764/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-23","New Enterprise Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what (a) qualifications and (b) experience are required to be an adviser on the New Enterprise Allowance programme.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","211720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100765","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-28","<p /> <p>The information requested is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-10-28T14:32:21.5390123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100765/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100765/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100765/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-23","Disability Living Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people have had the mobility component of their disability living allowance reduced in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","211704"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100766","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-28","<p>There have been no discussions between the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions and the Secretary of State for Defence on the exposure of HM armed forces to the risk of asbestos. HSE is not aware of any MOD asbestos-related issues that would have required this.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-10-28T17:09:30.9613697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100766/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100766/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100766/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-23","Armed Forces: Asbestos","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Defence on the exposure of armed forces to the risks of asbestos.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","211719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100767","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-29","<p /> <p>All staff undertake a 14 week training period in preparation for their role as DLA decision makers. This comprises a blend of classroom-based learning and on-the-job supervision and coaching.</p><p> </p><p>Following this 14 week training period continuing support is provided to decision makers through coaching, mentoring and monitoring, training workshops and workplace learning.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-10-29T15:10:41.1240943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100767/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100767/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100767/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-23","Disability Living Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what training is required before a disability living allowance decision-maker can take up the role.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","211705"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100768","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-28","<p /> <p>Since 2009, 120 inspectors have been trained to inspect licensed asbestos removal work. This training provides inspectors with appropriate knowledge and information to enable them to inspect such work safely and effectively.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-10-28T11:32:30.3922316Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100768/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100768/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100768/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-23","Asbestos","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many Health and Safety Executive inspectors have received training on the removal of asbestos from licensed premises since 2009.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","211717"
