"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100298","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-11-04","<p>Over the summer Ministers and officials undertook extensive discussions with a wide range of stakeholders regarding changes to DSA.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-11-04T15:37:59.6531348Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100298/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100298/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100298/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-10-22","Disabled Students' Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what representations he has received calling for a public consultation on proposed changes to disabled students' allowance.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","211565"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100299","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-29","<p>Tata have announced the signing of a Memorandum of Understanding with Klesch Group about a possible sale of their Long Products Division. Both companies have made clear that there are some months of commercial negotiation ahead including consultations with the workforce.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government and the Scottish Government have ongoing discussions on these and other matters all the time.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-10-29T16:53:12.8638043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100299/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100299/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100299/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-10-22","Tata Steel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Urgent Question on 16 October 2014, Official Report, column 445, on Tata Steel, what meetings and discussions (a) he and (b) Ministers in his Department have had with the Scottish Government to discuss the selling of the Long Products Division.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","211567"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100300","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-28","<p>UK Export Finance is supporting Mourne Ltd’s contract in relation to the upgrade of Kotoka International Airport. UK exports supported include lighting, steel frames, drainage pipes, engineering and design services.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-10-28T15:59:03.6882536Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100300/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100300/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100300/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100300/answer/previousversion/24562","Biography information for Matt Hancock","26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-10-22","Exports: Ghana","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what exports from the UK were supported by UK Export Finance's loan guarantee for Mourne Ltd's Kotoka International Airport project in Ghana.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","211503"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100301","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-30","<p>I can confirm that neither I nor my Rt Hon Friend the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills have received any such representations.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-10-30T16:28:30.1009586Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100301/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100301/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100301/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100301/answer/previousversion/24558","Biography information for Matt Hancock","26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-10-22","Oil: Western Sahara","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what representations he has received on consultations held with the Saharawi regarding proposed drilling for oil by Cairn Energy in the waters of Western Sahara.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Corbyn","Islington North","Jeremy Corbyn","211504"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100302","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-30","<p>Discussions are underway with the higher education sector to ensure institutions are ready to meet their legal duties under the Equality Act 2010 in respect of the changes for 2015/16 and 2016/17. The Higher Education Funding Council for England (HEFCE) is currently undertaking a review of provision and support for disabled students in higher education which will help to inform this.</p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-10-30T15:26:51.1857109Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100302/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100302/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100302/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-10-22","Students: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment his Department has made of the support offered to potential university students with a disability to ensure that they are able to access support in undertaking their studies.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","211519"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100303","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-30","<p>The Higher Education Funding Council for England is undertaking studies looking at how Institutions support students with specific disabilities and learning difficulties where intensive or multiagency support is required.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Association of Graduate Careers Advisory Services (AGCAS) supports a number of specialist task groups including a Disability Task Group (DTG) which promotes professional practice and provides information and training concerning the employability of disabled students and graduates.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-10-30T15:38:23.1828351Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100303/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100303/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100303/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-10-22","Students: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment his Department has made of the capacity of the Higher Education Funding Council for England to (a) support and (b) challenge universities which do not provide careers advice, counselling, financial advice to students with a disability and other support services.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","211520"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100304","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-11-04","<p>A variety of information is already available to students, both through the Unistats website - <a href="http://unistats.direct.gov.uk/" target="_blank">http://unistats.direct.gov.uk/</a> - and from individual Institutions. Institutions are considering what additional information may be necessary in light of the announcement on changes to the Disabled Students’ Allowance.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-11-04T17:00:55.0571365Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100304/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100304/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100304/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-10-22","Students: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will take steps to ensure that disabled pupils have information in advance of an application to a higher education institution on what reasonable adjustments that institution will make to meet their needs.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","211563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100305","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-30","<p>There are already a number of rights of appeal available to students.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government is working with interested parties to consider if further changes are needed.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-10-30T15:28:04.8500012Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100305/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100305/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100305/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-10-22","Students: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will bring forward proposals to give disabled pupils a right of appeal against higher education institutions at a special educational needs and disability tribunal where an institution fails to make reasonable adjustments under the Equality Act 2010.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","211564"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100306","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-29","<p>My Rt. Hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills is planning to visit Bassetlaw on Thursday 27 November.</p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson",,"2014-10-29T14:30:51.0132019Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100306/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100306/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100306/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-10-22","Bassetlaw","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, when he next plans to visit local businesses in Bassetlaw.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","211421"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100307","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-28","<p>The Government has consistently pushed for an ambitious agreement under the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership negotiations in line with the recently published mandate.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The European Commission has explicitly ruled out public services from the scope of any market liberalisation in TTIP, and it has therefore not been necessary to discuss any exclusions related to specific public services.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Commission has provided further details on the treatment of public services, available online at: <a href="http://trade.ec.europa.eu/doclib/docs/2014/may/tradoc_152462.pdf" target="_blank">http://trade.ec.europa.eu/doclib/docs/2014/may/tradoc_152462.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-10-28T16:04:43.4543869Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100307/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100307/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100307/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100307/answer/previousversion/24563","Biography information for Matt Hancock","26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-10-22","Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what work his Department has conducted on identifying specific policy areas and sectors for which the UK will seek exemptions from the scope of the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership; and what representations the UK has made to the EU on exemption of such policy areas or sectors.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","211430"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100308","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-11-04","<p>This information is not held centrally.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-11-04T16:40:12.0147519Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100308/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100308/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100308/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-10-22","Mass Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many responses his Department's press office has made to enquiries from student journalists in the last year.","false","Biography information for Austin Mitchell","Great Grimsby","Austin Mitchell","211446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100309","Cabinet Office","false","2014-10-27","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2014-10-27T14:45:32.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100309/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100309/answer","PQ 211557 ONS 364.pdf","PQ 211557 ONS 364.pdf","ONS Letter to Member - SMEs","ONS Letter to Member - SMEs","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100309/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-10-22","Small Businesses: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many small and medium-sized enterprises have premises in (a) Pendle, (b) Lancashire and (c) the North West.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","211557"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100310","Cabinet Office","false","2014-10-29","<p>My Rt Hon Friend the Minister of State for Culture and the Digital Economy updated the House on the work the government is undertaking to address the issue of misleading websites during a Westminster Hall Debate on 28 October 2014.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","212074 ; 212075 ; 212076 ; 212077 ; 212078 ; 212079 ; 212080 ; 212081 ; 212082 ; 212083","2014-10-29T17:02:14.4637908Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100310/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100310/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100310/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-10-22","Electronic Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what progress his Department has made in tackling copycat websites which charge extra for government services.","false","Biography information for Chris Evans","Islwyn","Chris Evans","211552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100311","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-03","<p>The Government takes the enforcement of the National Minimum Wage (NMW) very seriously.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC does not keep data in a format to enable provision of the statistics requested on the amount of arrears paid or not paid to workers. HMRC contacts every employer whom they find has paid workers below the National Minimum Wage to confirm that they have paid the identified arrears to the workers. In addition, where it has found arrears for five or fewer workers it will contact all the workers to confirm payment by the employer. In cases involving arrears for more than five workers it will contact a minimum sample of five workers to confirm payment by the employer. HMRC will pursue non-payment of arrears through civil recovery action.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC review every complaint that is referred to them by the Pay and Work Rights Helpline and will always investigate any case of possible National Minimum Wage abuse. Therefore there will always be variation in the number of cases investigated within specific sectors.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","211547 ; 211653","2014-11-03T15:22:53.7580979Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100311/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100311/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100311/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-10-22","Social Services: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much of the national minimum wage arrears identified in the social care sector by HM Revenue and Customs in the findings of its social care evaluation of November 2013 have been recovered and paid to the workers affected.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","211605"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100312","HM Treasury","false","2014-10-27","<p>Increasing the National insurance Contribution Primary threshold for employees and Lower Profits Limit for self employed to £10,000 in 2014-15, in order to match the personal allowance, would take an estimated 1.5m people out of paying NICs.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>These estimates are based on the 2011-12 Survey of Personal Incomes projected forward to 2014-15 using economic assumptions consistent with the OBR’s March 2014 economic and fiscal outlook.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-10-27T16:26:00.4546072Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100312/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100312/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100312/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-10-22","Income Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will estimate how many people would not be paying income tax and national insurance contributions if the threshold for both were equalised at the higher rate of the two.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","211580"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100313","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-10","<p>This information is not available.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>I refer my hon. friend to the reply given on 1 May 2014, Official report, columns 799W-800W,</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201314/cmhansrd/cm140501/text/140501w0002.htm#14050155000316" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201314/cmhansrd/cm140501/text/140501w0002.htm#14050155000316</a></p><p> </p><p>for the number of families claiming tax credits where, if claiming as a couple, at least one of the family members was recorded as being a non-UK national when they registered for a National Insurance number (NINO).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>These awards will include people who were recorded as being a non-UK national when they first registered for a NINO but now have UK nationality. The information cannot therefore be used to reliably determine the number of non-UK nationals in receipt of tax credits and was not intended to be used for that purpose.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2014-11-10T17:47:02.4187147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100313/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100313/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100313/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-10-22","Working Tax Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many non-UK citizens from (a) other EU countries and (b) the rest of the world are in receipt of working tax credit.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","211619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100314","HM Treasury","false","2014-10-29","<p>I refer the hon member to the answer that I gave on 24 October to the hon member for South Down:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=208391" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=208391</a></p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2014-10-29T14:43:05.9638559Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100314/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100314/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100314/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-10-22","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department has approved (a) the strategic outline business case and (b) the full business case for universal credit.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","211587"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100315","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-03","<p>The Government takes the enforcement of the National Minimum Wage (NMW) very seriously.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC does not keep data in a format to enable provision of the statistics requested on the amount of arrears paid or not paid to workers. HMRC contacts every employer whom they find has paid workers below the National Minimum Wage to confirm that they have paid the identified arrears to the workers. In addition, where it has found arrears for five or fewer workers it will contact all the workers to confirm payment by the employer. In cases involving arrears for more than five workers it will contact a minimum sample of five workers to confirm payment by the employer. HMRC will pursue non-payment of arrears through civil recovery action.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC review every complaint that is referred to them by the Pay and Work Rights Helpline and will always investigate any case of possible National Minimum Wage abuse. Therefore there will always be variation in the number of cases investigated within specific sectors.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","211605 ; 211653","2014-11-03T15:22:53.851797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100315/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100315/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100315/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-10-22","Home Care Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 17 October 2014 to Question 209191, for what reason fewer HM Revenue and Customs investigations into the home-care sector were carried out in 2013-14 than 2012-13.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","211547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100316","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-18","<p>Her Majesty’s Revenue and Customs (HMRC) includes information on bank charges in its annual report and accounts (Page 138 Other Administration Costs and Page 140 Programme Costs):</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/330670/HMRC-annual-report-2013-14.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/330670/HMRC-annual-report-2013-14.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2014-11-18T15:31:39.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100316/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100316/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100316/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-10-22","Bank Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much his Department spent on bank transfer transactions for tax credits and tax refunds in the last financial year.","false","Biography information for Ian Swales","Redcar","Ian Swales","211413"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100317","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-29","<p>The earnings threshold in Carer’s Allowance is regularly reviewed. It is designed to enable carers to maintain a link with the labour market and achieve greater financial independence. It is increased periodically, most recently from £100 to £102 on 20 May 2014.</p><p> </p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-10-29T17:42:37.6084177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100317/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100317/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100317/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-10-22","Carer's Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will make it his policy to link an increase of the earnings threshold for carer's allowance to the rise in the National Minimum Wage.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","211436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100318","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-03","<p>The Government takes the enforcement of the National Minimum Wage (NMW) very seriously.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC does not keep data in a format to enable provision of the statistics requested on the amount of arrears paid or not paid to workers. HMRC contacts every employer whom they find has paid workers below the National Minimum Wage to confirm that they have paid the identified arrears to the workers. In addition, where it has found arrears for five or fewer workers it will contact all the workers to confirm payment by the employer. In cases involving arrears for more than five workers it will contact a minimum sample of five workers to confirm payment by the employer. HMRC will pursue non-payment of arrears through civil recovery action.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC review every complaint that is referred to them by the Pay and Work Rights Helpline and will always investigate any case of possible National Minimum Wage abuse. Therefore there will always be variation in the number of cases investigated within specific sectors.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","211547 ; 211605","2014-11-03T15:22:54.2912799Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100318/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100318/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100318/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-10-22","Home Care Services: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 17 October 2014 to question 209191, how many investigations by HM Revenue and Customs into the home care sector were conducted in the first six months of 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","211653"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100319","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-10-28","<p>My Department takes seriously its responsibilities to respond to MP’s letters in a timely fashion. Having checked all of our databases I can find no record of the letter the rt. hon. Member for Warley refers to and I respectfully ask him to send me a copy so that I may respond.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-10-28T15:41:51.0751296Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100319/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100319/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100319/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-10-22","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he plans to reply to the letter of 24 July 2014 from the hon. Member for Warley, on compulsory purchase orders.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","Mr John Spellar","211411"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100320","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-02-23","<p>The last Administration failed to meet its Decent Homes target. It pledged in 2000 that: “We... are committed to ensuring that all social housing is of a decent standard within 10 years” (DETR, <em>Quality and Choice: A Decent Home for All: The Housing Green Paper</em>, April 2000, p.11). But 16 per cent of local authority homes were not decent by 2010.</p><p>That last Government also cut the Decent Homes programme by £150 million in July 2009, cannibalising the housing programme to pay for other policies. I also observe the last Prime Minister planned to cut back housing investment, remarking before the general election: “Housing is essentially a private sector activity. Let's be honest about this... I don't see a need for us to continue with such a big renovation programme” (<em>BBC Newsnight</em>, 30 April 2010).</p><p>However, the Coalition Government is investing £2.3 billion from 2011 to 2016 to improve the quality of existing social housing through the Decent Homes programme and large-scale voluntary transfer gap funding The funding is for clearing the backlog, and therefore is less than under the last Administration – as by intention, there should be an increasingly smaller number of homes to pay to refurbish.</p><p>The table below shows spending since 2005.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p>£ million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2004-05</p></td><td><p>£578</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2005-06</p></td><td><p>£864</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2006-07</p></td><td><p>£814</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007-08</p></td><td><p>£1,005</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008-09</p></td><td><p>£1,017</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009-10</p></td><td><p>£1,079</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>£756</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>£494</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>£563</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>£631</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>est. £532</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>NB. The figure for 14-15 contains £15 million funding for South Tyneside which was brought forward from the 2015-16 allocation.</p><p>The number of non-decent local authority dwellings across England has fallen from 292,000 in 1 April 2010 to 146,000 in April 2014, with a forecast of a further fall to 113,000 by April 2015. This shows clear progress in refurbishing these homes.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-02-23T16:51:14.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100320/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100320/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100320/answer","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100320/answer/previousversion/24440","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-10-22","Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what was spent on the Decent Homes Programme in each year since 2005.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","211623"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100321","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-10-29","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to my written answer of 21 October 2014, PQ 206256.</p><p> </p><p>Figures are held by local authority area, not parliamentary constituency.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-10-29T16:35:05.3525427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100321/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100321/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100321/answer","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100321/answer/previousversion/24450","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-10-22","Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many homes in (a) Bethnal Green and Bow constituency, (b) the borough of Tower Hamlets, (c) London and (d) England failed to meet the decent homes standard in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","211624"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100322","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-10-27","<p>My Rt Hon. Friend, the Secretary of State and myself routinely meet with Ministerial colleagues to discuss a range of matters.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant","211645 ; 211647","2014-10-27T12:25:41.1689393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100322/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100322/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/100322/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-10-22","Tourism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when he last met the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills to discuss tourism.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","211646"
